%% Diagram: Per-author undo with stack rewriting
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant CA as Client A
    participant MP as Server (Rust)
    participant CB as Client B

    Note over CA: A1 — change fill = red on object O
    CA->>MP: delta(O.fill = red, seq 10)
    MP-->>CB: broadcast(O.fill = red)

    Note over CB: B1 — change stroke = blue on object O
    CB->>MP: delta(O.stroke = blue, seq 11)
    MP-->>CA: broadcast(O.stroke = blue)

    Note over CA: A pushes A1 onto its local undo stack.<br/>B's edit lives on B's stack only.

    Note over CA: A presses Undo
    CA->>CA: Pop A1 from undo stack
    CA->>CA: Inverse op: O.fill = previous (gray)
    CA->>MP: delta(O.fill = gray, seq 12)

    Note over CA: Rewrite A's redo stack at undo time<br/>so a later Redo "puts back" red — but only<br/>over A's own subsequent edits, never over B's.

    MP-->>CB: broadcast(O.fill = gray)

    Note over CA: A presses Redo
    CA->>CA: Pop redo entry (red)
    CA->>CA: Rewrite A's undo stack at redo time
    CA->>MP: delta(O.fill = red, seq 13)
    MP-->>CB: broadcast(O.fill = red)

    Note over CA,CB: Invariant — undo many → copy → redo<br/>back to present must leave the document<br/>identical to the present state.
